cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.DC, cs.NE, cs.DS

This paper is about training deep neural networks on large-scale datasets, specifically ImageNet. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also focuses on computer vision tasks, which suggests cs.CV (Computer Vision) as the second most likely sub-category. The use of large-scale parallel computing and optimization algorithms also suggests cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as possible sub-categories. Finally, the paper presents experimental results and analysis, which suggests cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as a possible sub-category.
